summary:
[log#4] Method for
combining stones that we devised didn’t work for the fire stone as it is impervious
to heat, we had to use...
caption:
[log#4]

Method for combining stones that we devised didn’t work for the fire stone as it is impervious to heat, we had to use roundabout way by melting both stones in acid, surprisingly this worked well and stones combined without a hitch.

I think that this method affected the effects of the stone, as the specimen #4 looks more like poison type pokemon than fire type. Despite the looks however his types are normal/fire.

As of all evolutions of eevee flareon looks like it the most, we expected specimen #4 to look just like oversized version of its previous form, however result looks very different from our vision.

Body of specimen #4 gained additional veins, that has highly acidic liquid flowing through them. Temperature of the liquid is incredibly high, and during the evolution some veins explode from the heat resulting in the scalding of the surrounding areas of the body.

The tongue of specimen transformed into its crest, which I suppose was intended to replicate tuft on the head of flareons. It has tube like growth on it which can spew acidic liquid from its body.

Also tail has “grown” and also has a hole in the tip which can spew acid too.

[log end]
